net.objectof.model

Interface Id<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Named
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IBaseId, ICategory, IGeo, IId, ILocation, IMember, IOther, IPerson, IProperty, IResource, ISchema

    public interface Id<T>
extends Named
    An Id identifies a Resource object. Resources are uniquely identified through the unique combination of a Kind and label object. Labels are expected to be simple objects such as Numbers or Strings.

    It is strongly recommended that when implementing an Id, the equals() method performs:

    this.kind().equals(a.kind()) && this.label().equals(a.label())

    As per Java's general recommendation, the hashCode() method should be overridden as well.

    Author:
    jdh
